  "target_response": {
    "text": "Burning lungs during 400m repeats can be normal — uncomfortable by design, not automatically damage. At that intensity you move a lot of air quickly, your airways can dry and cool, and the effort often creates that burning sensation during the rep. The tell that yours is the benign kind is the timing: it lives inside the hard reps and eases within minutes once the session ends. The pattern that would deserve a doctor's look is different — wheezing, a cough that hangs around long after training, chest tightness at rest, or breathlessness far out of proportion to the effort. If it is just rep-time burn that vanishes with the cooldown, log it as interval effort and keep the next easy day easy.",
